1
00:01:30,960 --> 00:01:35,039
[Dream of Golden Years]

2
00:01:35,700 --> 00:01:39,070
[2006]

3
00:01:47,039 --> 00:01:48,100
Miss, you're here.

4
00:01:48,590 --> 00:01:49,789
Which bunk are you in?

5
00:01:50,039 --> 00:01:51,310
Uh... No. 6.

6
00:01:51,840 --> 00:01:52,840
No. 6 is over here.

7
00:01:53,509 --> 00:01:54,570
We're in this bunk.

8
00:01:54,840 --> 00:01:55,870
We'll be classmates from now on.

9
00:01:55,870 --> 00:01:57,229
Let's look out for each other.

10
00:01:57,229 --> 00:01:57,700
Is that heavy?

11
00:01:57,700 --> 00:01:58,479
Do you need a hand?

12
00:01:58,479 --> 00:01:59,039
No, thanks!

13
00:01:59,039 --> 00:01:59,840
I can manage.

14
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:00,860
Be careful.

15
00:02:01,070 --> 00:02:01,430
Okay.

16
00:02:02,840 --> 00:02:04,170
Miss, what's your name?

17
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:05,040
Where are you from?

18
00:02:05,040 --> 00:02:06,870
Didn't your parents come with you?

19
00:02:06,870 --> 00:02:07,430
Mom,

20
00:02:07,430 --> 00:02:08,680
let her put her things down

21
00:02:08,680 --> 00:02:10,680
before you start your questioning.

22
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:11,840
Hello, Auntie.

23
00:02:11,840 --> 00:02:13,100
My name is Xia Xiaolan.

24
00:02:13,680 --> 00:02:15,560
I'm from Xiangsheng.

25
00:02:15,630 --> 00:02:17,840
My parents work in geology,

26
00:02:17,840 --> 00:02:18,630
and they're away on a business trip,

27
00:02:18,630 --> 00:02:19,690
so I came by myself.

28
00:02:21,560 --> 00:02:22,470
Hello, Xiaolan.

29
00:02:22,470 --> 00:02:23,310
I'm Zhao Lin.

30
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:25,360
I'm from Ganzhou, Jiangxi.

31
00:02:25,870 --> 00:02:26,680
Sorry about that.

32
00:02:26,680 --> 00:02:28,240
Both my parents are teachers,

33
00:02:28,240 --> 00:02:29,470
so they tend to talk a lot.

34
00:02:29,470 --> 00:02:30,070
It's fine.

35
00:02:30,630 --> 00:02:31,560
Do you need help?

36
00:02:31,630 --> 00:02:32,090
No need.

37
00:02:32,280 --> 00:02:32,590
No need.

38
00:02:32,590 --> 00:02:33,590
Your parents' work

39
00:02:33,590 --> 00:02:34,680
must be quite demanding.

40
00:02:34,680 --> 00:02:36,000
You're so considerate.

41
00:02:36,000 --> 00:02:36,660
Look at you—

42
00:02:36,910 --> 00:02:38,630
you can't even make your own bed,

43
00:02:38,630 --> 00:02:40,000
and you're already a university student.

44
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:41,150
Mom, stop it.

45
00:02:41,150 --> 00:02:42,470
Don't embarrass me.

46
00:02:43,710 --> 00:02:45,710
I fabricated my family background,

47
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:47,860
thinking I could start a new life.

48
00:02:48,680 --> 00:02:50,940
But the lies only dressed up the surface—

49
00:02:51,590 --> 00:02:52,790
the substance of life

50
00:02:53,310 --> 00:02:55,640
still needs to be filled with real effort.

51
00:03:02,040 --> 00:03:05,270
[Episode 24: A Fabricated Life]

52
00:03:06,310 --> 00:03:08,470
Anyone who's found gold,

53
00:03:08,710 --> 00:03:10,970
please line up to register and turn it in!

54
00:03:11,190 --> 00:03:12,710
Thank you for your cooperation!

55
00:03:12,710 --> 00:03:13,750
Thank you, everyone!

56
00:03:13,750 --> 00:03:14,610
Hello, Ms. Xia.

57
00:03:14,680 --> 00:03:15,310
We heard gold

58
00:03:15,310 --> 00:03:16,520
was discovered here.

59
00:03:16,630 --> 00:03:17,960
What are your thoughts on this?

60
00:03:17,960 --> 00:03:19,150
All found gold must be turned in!

61
00:03:19,150 --> 00:03:20,430
Follow me!

62
00:03:20,450 --> 00:03:21,520
Come on, let's go!

63
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:23,050
Let's go take back our gold!

64
00:03:23,470 --> 00:03:23,930
Come on!

65
00:03:24,120 --> 00:03:25,720
No one is allowed to keep any!

66
00:03:26,310 --> 00:03:27,280
What are you doing?

67
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:28,210
Stop, all of you!

68
00:03:28,840 --> 00:03:29,400
Calm down!

69
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:30,520
That's my family's gold!

70
00:03:30,520 --> 00:03:31,190
Calm down!

71
00:03:31,190 --> 00:03:33,360
It's my family's gold!

72
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:34,890
It's our Luo family's gold!

73
00:03:35,030 --> 00:03:35,750
It's mine!

74
00:03:39,190 --> 00:03:40,250
Grandpa? Grandpa!

75
00:03:40,880 --> 00:03:41,410
Careful.

76
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:43,079
Get him to the hospital now!

77
00:03:43,079 --> 00:03:43,880
Hurry, hurry!

78
00:03:45,850 --> 00:03:46,630
As you can see,

79
00:03:46,630 --> 00:03:47,680
I am currently at

80
00:03:47,680 --> 00:03:49,710
the Golden Sands Pool project
construction site.

81
00:03:49,710 --> 00:03:51,470
According to police reports,

82
00:03:51,710 --> 00:03:53,240
a total of 627 grams of gold

83
00:03:53,240 --> 00:03:54,870
was found in the area.

84
00:03:55,400 --> 00:03:57,460
Six hundred and twenty-seven grams.

85
00:03:57,710 --> 00:03:59,310
We buried a kilogram of gold—

86
00:03:59,520 --> 00:04:01,030
the loss is quite significant.

87
00:04:01,030 --> 00:04:02,750
Yuesheng's geological survey department

88
00:04:02,750 --> 00:04:04,000
is about to conduct

89
00:04:04,030 --> 00:04:05,000
a professional

90
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:06,030
assessment here

91
00:04:06,050 --> 00:04:08,280
to determine whether there is a gold mine

92
00:04:08,280 --> 00:04:10,150
underground with commercial value.

93
00:04:10,150 --> 00:04:10,750
Ms. Xia,

94
00:04:10,870 --> 00:04:12,400
your eye for property is amazing!

95
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:14,310
This really is a feng shui treasure land.

96
00:04:14,310 --> 00:04:14,960
Now,

97
00:04:14,960 --> 00:04:16,820
Golden Sands Pool is well-known!

98
00:04:17,160 --> 00:04:18,190
Who would have thought back then

99
00:04:18,190 --> 00:04:19,380
that such a stinky bamboo ditch

100
00:04:19,380 --> 00:04:20,839
actually contained gold?

101
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:23,040
Qi Hang's first project

102
00:04:23,160 --> 00:04:24,290
is about to take off.

103
00:04:25,510 --> 00:04:26,630
Now that the name is out there,

104
00:04:26,630 --> 00:04:28,490
the money will naturally follow.

105
00:04:28,630 --> 00:04:30,240
Xiaolan is amazing.

106
00:04:30,710 --> 00:04:32,110
There really is gold-bearing sand.

107
00:04:32,110 --> 00:04:32,950
Look,

108
00:04:33,240 --> 00:04:35,000
it's even in the newspaper.

109
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:36,150
[From Stinky Bamboo Ditch to
Gold-Laden Land: Wasteland Yields Gold;]

110
00:04:35,510 --> 00:04:36,360
I always said it—

111
00:04:36,150 --> 00:04:36,909
[Qi Hang Property's Project Strikes Gold—
Golden Sands Pool Lives Up to Its Name]

112
00:04:36,390 --> 00:04:37,070
Xiaolan

113
00:04:37,070 --> 00:04:38,510
can pull off anything.

114
00:04:39,390 --> 00:04:40,390
They found gold

115
00:04:40,390 --> 00:04:41,430
on that plot?

116
00:04:43,630 --> 00:04:45,600
How does that even happen?

117
00:04:46,190 --> 00:04:47,650
This makes no difference.

118
00:04:47,920 --> 00:04:49,159
This might not be bad news

119
00:04:49,159 --> 00:04:50,159
for us, sir.

120
00:04:51,159 --> 00:04:52,240
The piece of land

121
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:54,390
is next to our golf course.

122
00:04:54,480 --> 00:04:55,870
How did we not know about

123
00:04:55,870 --> 00:04:57,159
this spot before?

124
00:05:01,720 --> 00:05:02,630
I'm sorry,

125
00:05:02,870 --> 00:05:04,630
but I haven't received

126
00:05:04,650 --> 00:05:06,870
any instructions
regarding selling the land.

127
00:05:06,870 --> 00:05:08,680
Could you leave

128
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:10,950
your contact details
if it would be convenient?

129
00:05:10,950 --> 00:05:12,600
And may I ask what your offer?

130
00:05:12,830 --> 00:05:14,720
I can pass it along to my boss.

131
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:16,250
Alright.

132
00:05:16,750 --> 00:05:19,040
I'll get back to you if there are updates.

133
00:05:19,310 --> 00:05:19,840
Goodbye.

134
00:05:25,600 --> 00:05:26,000
You Li.

135
00:05:27,430 --> 00:05:27,950
Ms. Xia,

136
00:05:28,630 --> 00:05:29,390
several

137
00:05:29,390 --> 00:05:30,190
real estate companies

138
00:05:30,190 --> 00:05:30,800
have called asking

139
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:32,360
if we're selling Golden Sands Pool.

140
00:05:32,360 --> 00:05:33,040
The highest offer

141
00:05:33,040 --> 00:05:34,370
has reached 12 million!

142
00:05:35,070 --> 00:05:35,870
The highest offer

143
00:05:35,870 --> 00:05:37,720
is from the American Wilson Group?

144
00:05:37,720 --> 00:05:38,040
Yes,

145
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:39,159
the developer

146
00:05:39,159 --> 00:05:40,480
of the golf course.

147
00:05:41,360 --> 00:05:42,600
Okay, let's go with them.

148
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:43,730
Contact them for me.

149
00:05:44,310 --> 00:05:46,190
Are we really going to sell that plot?

150
00:05:46,190 --> 00:05:47,159
Of course not.

151
00:05:47,830 --> 00:05:48,720
That's the great place our Ms. Xia

152
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:50,240
spotted at first glance.

153
00:05:51,000 --> 00:05:52,030
Our Ms. Xia

154
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:53,950
is a businessperson with vision—

155
00:05:53,950 --> 00:05:54,870
she wants to build buildings,

156
00:05:54,870 --> 00:05:56,310
not flip land for a quick profit.

157
00:05:56,310 --> 00:05:57,970
How could she just turn around

158
00:05:58,360 --> 00:05:59,560
and sell it for a markup?

159
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:00,580
Our Attorney Zhou is

160
00:06:00,580 --> 00:06:02,930
really perceptive about people.

161
00:06:03,950 --> 00:06:05,720
Then why do you want to meet

162
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:06,830
with that American businessman?

163
00:06:06,830 --> 00:06:07,960
You'll know in time.

164
00:06:08,480 --> 00:06:09,140
Zhou Cheng,

165
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:11,430
have I been moving

166
00:06:11,430 --> 00:06:12,390
too fast lately?

167
00:06:13,950 --> 00:06:14,750
Yes, too fast.

168
00:06:15,270 --> 00:06:16,800
So fast you're about to fly.

169
00:06:18,920 --> 00:06:19,480
Ms. Xia,

170
00:06:19,740 --> 00:06:20,530
we heard gold

171
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:21,800
was discovered here.

172
00:06:21,830 --> 00:06:23,560
What are your thoughts on this?

173
00:06:23,830 --> 00:06:24,190
Yes.

174
00:06:24,480 --> 00:06:25,630
We'll let the Futian Subdistrict Office

175
00:06:25,630 --> 00:06:27,430
keep the gold we found for now.

176
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,560
As for the construction site...

177
00:06:29,560 --> 00:06:30,920
we'll suspend work temporarily

178
00:06:30,920 --> 00:06:32,240
and invite the geological survey team

179
00:06:32,240 --> 00:06:33,040
to come and determine

180
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:35,440
whether there's actually a gold mine here.

181
00:06:35,750 --> 00:06:36,920
I'd bet anything

182
00:06:37,870 --> 00:06:38,510
that you buried

183
00:06:38,510 --> 00:06:39,950
that gold yourself.

184
00:06:41,560 --> 00:06:43,190
Xia Xiaolan, oh Xia Xiaolan.

185
00:06:43,190 --> 00:06:44,159
Did you know beforehand

186
00:06:44,159 --> 00:06:45,360
that there was gold here?

187
00:06:45,360 --> 00:06:47,040
You're still so full of schemes.

188
00:06:47,040 --> 00:06:47,600
No.

189
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:49,630
Although I'd heard

190
00:06:49,630 --> 00:06:51,360
the legend of "gold-bearing sand
springing from the ground,"

191
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:52,360
I chose this name

192
00:06:52,360 --> 00:06:53,560
purely for good luck.

193
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:54,950
I never imagined it would actually happen.

194
00:06:54,950 --> 00:06:55,920
Xia Xiaolan,

195
00:06:56,560 --> 00:06:57,120
just how many tricks

196
00:06:57,120 --> 00:06:58,580
do you have up your sleeve?

197
00:06:59,480 --> 00:07:00,870
Good thing I was smart enough

198
00:07:00,870 --> 00:07:02,030
to choose to partner with you

199
00:07:02,030 --> 00:07:03,520
rather than against you.

200
00:07:04,430 --> 00:07:04,990
Cheers.

201
00:07:16,390 --> 00:07:18,000
Alright, I'll call you when I need you.

202
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:18,750
Okay, Mr. Ge.

203
00:07:19,920 --> 00:07:20,270
Ms. Xia.

204
00:07:20,270 --> 00:07:21,070
Are things ready

205
00:07:21,070 --> 00:07:22,390
with Uncle and Director Pan?

206
00:07:22,390 --> 00:07:24,070
Uncle arranged a meeting
with Director Pan long ago.

207
00:07:24,070 --> 00:07:25,360
They are in the private room next door.

208
00:07:25,360 --> 00:07:25,750
Okay.

209
00:07:29,510 --> 00:07:30,160
Ms. Xia,

210
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:34,270
you're even more stunning in real life
than on TV.

211
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:36,920
You must be Mr. Wilson.

212
00:07:38,190 --> 00:07:39,830
I've heard that Americans

213
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:41,830
are good at complimenting women.

214
00:07:42,360 --> 00:07:43,680
It is so nice to

215
00:07:43,700 --> 00:07:44,780
hear it today.

216
00:07:45,070 --> 00:07:47,070
I did not realize your English

217
00:07:47,070 --> 00:07:48,430
is so fluent, Ms. Xia.

218
00:07:48,750 --> 00:07:49,510
Thank you.

219
00:07:49,920 --> 00:07:51,520
But I'm afraid that flattery

220
00:07:51,720 --> 00:07:53,920
won't get you a discount

221
00:07:53,950 --> 00:07:55,880
on Jinshachi (Golden Sands Pool).

222
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:57,360
Beautiful and witty.

223
00:07:57,360 --> 00:07:57,820
Please.

224
00:07:59,159 --> 00:08:00,890
Well, it's an honor to meet you.

225
00:08:07,360 --> 00:08:07,820
Cheers.

226
00:08:07,920 --> 00:08:08,430
Cheers.

227
00:08:13,600 --> 00:08:14,160
Ms. Xia,

228
00:08:14,750 --> 00:08:20,630
business... It naturally has
a big element of luck.

229
00:08:21,390 --> 00:08:23,600
And you seem to have plenty of it.

230
00:08:24,190 --> 00:08:25,560
You're buying

231
00:08:26,040 --> 00:08:26,950
that plot of land

232
00:08:26,950 --> 00:08:28,270
that conveniently runs next to

233
00:08:28,270 --> 00:08:29,390
my golf course.

234
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:32,840
Somewhat of the convenience
when you think.

235
00:08:34,030 --> 00:08:35,390
Are you implying

236
00:08:35,390 --> 00:08:36,440
that I've been riding the coattails of

237
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:38,169
your golf course development?

238
00:08:38,600 --> 00:08:41,360
Let's not dwell on history.
Now, we're here.

239
00:08:43,640 --> 00:08:44,670
Look, even if you did buy

240
00:08:44,670 --> 00:08:46,120
that plot of land just to

241
00:08:46,120 --> 00:08:47,510
flip it for a high price,

242
00:08:47,580 --> 00:08:48,440
I would say that you're

243
00:08:48,440 --> 00:08:50,390
a very smart businesswoman.

244
00:08:50,550 --> 00:08:53,980
I wouldn't mind that.
It's just three acres, more or less.

245
00:08:54,240 --> 00:08:55,030
If I

246
00:08:56,080 --> 00:08:59,120
buy it for 12 million dollars...

247
00:09:00,320 --> 00:09:01,320
it's not much of a challenge

248
00:09:01,320 --> 00:09:02,520
for the Wilson Group.

249
00:09:03,630 --> 00:09:04,720
So you're saying

250
00:09:04,720 --> 00:09:05,670
I bought that land

251
00:09:05,670 --> 00:09:07,890
specifically to squeeze money out of you?

252
00:09:07,890 --> 00:09:09,690
Then should I thank you

253
00:09:09,720 --> 00:09:10,750
for your generosity

254
00:09:10,750 --> 00:09:11,840
and leniency?

255
00:09:14,150 --> 00:09:15,910
How do you say it in Chinese?

256
00:09:17,000 --> 00:09:20,680
"Duh leh pyen-ee hi my guy"
(cashing in and pretending not to notice).

257
00:09:20,680 --> 00:09:22,450
I know exactly what you paid

258
00:09:22,480 --> 00:09:23,680
for that plot of land.

259
00:09:23,830 --> 00:09:24,600
Wedge between

260
00:09:24,600 --> 00:09:25,480
the golf course

261
00:09:25,740 --> 00:09:27,220
and the resort.

262
00:09:27,630 --> 00:09:28,240
Selling it to me

263
00:09:28,240 --> 00:09:29,370
is your best option.

264
00:09:29,800 --> 00:09:30,930
But if I...

265
00:09:31,030 --> 00:09:32,840
Hello, everybody!

266
00:09:34,910 --> 00:09:36,170
Having a big meal here?

267
00:09:36,680 --> 00:09:37,940
Talking big business?

268
00:09:38,510 --> 00:09:39,750
Sorry, I'm late.

269
00:09:40,000 --> 00:09:41,800
I'll punish myself with a drink.

270
00:09:42,550 --> 00:09:43,790
Let me drink one as an apology.

271
00:09:43,790 --> 00:09:44,740
Ms. Xia, who is this?

272
00:09:44,740 --> 00:09:45,740
Hold on, hold on!

273
00:09:46,000 --> 00:09:46,930
Hold on a minute.

274
00:09:49,600 --> 00:09:50,120
Look.

275
00:09:50,510 --> 00:09:52,240
This has nothing to do with her.

276
00:09:52,290 --> 00:09:53,550
I came of my own accord.

277
00:09:53,630 --> 00:09:54,630
Because if not,

278
00:09:55,240 --> 00:09:57,550
you would've gotten
Jinshachi (Golden Sands Pool).

279
00:09:57,550 --> 00:09:58,950
Let me introduce myself.

280
00:09:59,080 --> 00:10:00,940
I'm Mr. Du, from Chengrong Group.

281
00:10:02,270 --> 00:10:03,270
So, Mr. Wilson,

282
00:10:03,750 --> 00:10:06,600
I heard that you offered 12 million?

283
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:13,630
I'm gonna offer 18 million!

284
00:10:14,550 --> 00:10:15,880
In Chinese, we call that

285
00:10:16,150 --> 00:10:17,200
18 million—

286
00:10:17,440 --> 00:10:18,600
"sure to prosper!"

287
00:10:19,240 --> 00:10:20,440
How about it, Ms. Xia?

288
00:10:20,600 --> 00:10:21,660
If you are willing,

289
00:10:21,720 --> 00:10:23,240
we can sign the contract right now.

290
00:10:23,240 --> 00:10:23,720
Hua.

291
00:10:26,320 --> 00:10:26,980
Du Zhaohui,

292
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:27,860
that's enough.

293
00:10:29,670 --> 00:10:30,510
Ms. Xia,

294
00:10:31,030 --> 00:10:33,150
if you weren't happy with my offer,

295
00:10:33,150 --> 00:10:35,720
we might've continued to negotiate.

296
00:10:36,240 --> 00:10:37,100
But this kind of

297
00:10:37,510 --> 00:10:40,030
last-minute price adjustment...

298
00:10:40,270 --> 00:10:42,240
That's extremely disrespectful.

299
00:10:42,330 --> 00:10:43,960
We've got nothing more to talk about here.

300
00:10:43,960 --> 00:10:44,840
Mr. Wilson!

301
00:10:45,870 --> 00:10:46,390
Goodbye!

302
00:10:46,390 --> 00:10:47,280
Have a good day!

303
00:10:47,360 --> 00:10:47,720
Bye-bye.

304
00:10:47,720 --> 00:10:48,920
Ge Jian, see them out.

305
00:10:51,910 --> 00:10:52,640
How was that?

306
00:10:53,720 --> 00:10:55,320
I put on a good show, didn't I?

307
00:10:56,120 --> 00:10:57,050
Why are you here?

308
00:10:57,080 --> 00:10:58,440
To help you drive up the price.

309
00:10:58,440 --> 00:11:00,030
Didn't I pull that off flawlessly?

310
00:11:00,030 --> 00:11:01,090
Drive up the price?

311
00:11:01,150 --> 00:11:02,550
You drove the buyer away.

312
00:11:03,150 --> 00:11:04,150
Let him go.

313
00:11:05,000 --> 00:11:06,960
It's not like
you were really going to sell to him.

314
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:08,110
Knowing you as I do,

315
00:11:08,670 --> 00:11:09,200
I suppose

316
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:10,510
the real buyer is...

317
00:11:22,240 --> 00:11:23,040
Director Pan,

318
00:11:23,150 --> 00:11:23,720
you see,

319
00:11:24,320 --> 00:11:26,520
that's basically the whole situation.

320
00:11:27,470 --> 00:11:27,860
Okay.

321
00:11:28,200 --> 00:11:29,360
I won't say much else.

322
00:11:29,360 --> 00:11:31,510
Let me go back and think about it.

323
00:11:31,750 --> 00:11:34,080
No matter how much we hype up
Golden Sands Pool,

324
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:36,270
it's all pointless
if we can't convince the bank.

325
00:11:36,270 --> 00:11:37,440
It's useless for us to claim

326
00:11:37,440 --> 00:11:38,870
Golden Sands Pool is worth 10 million.

327
00:11:38,870 --> 00:11:39,600
We have to make the person

328
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:41,750
responsible for loans at the bank
believe it.

329
00:11:41,750 --> 00:11:42,750
So, on the day I meet

330
00:11:42,750 --> 00:11:43,550
with Harold,

331
00:11:43,960 --> 00:11:44,720
Uncle, you'll handle the negotiations

332
00:11:44,720 --> 00:11:46,270
with the loan officers.

333
00:11:46,910 --> 00:11:47,640
Understood.

334
00:11:48,460 --> 00:11:49,600
I'll arrange a meeting later with

335
00:11:49,600 --> 00:11:50,630
Director Pan from the bank.

336
00:11:50,630 --> 00:11:52,400
Let's not talk about work today.

337
00:11:52,400 --> 00:11:53,390
Just the two of us brothers,

338
00:11:53,390 --> 00:11:54,240
let's drink till we drop.

339
00:11:54,240 --> 00:11:54,770
Alright!

340
00:11:54,790 --> 00:11:55,120
Come on, cheers!

341
00:11:55,120 --> 00:11:56,080
Come on, drink!

342
00:11:56,360 --> 00:11:56,820
Cheers!

343
00:11:56,960 --> 00:11:57,420
Come on!

344
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:02,280
You downed it!

345
00:12:02,550 --> 00:12:03,960
Don't act like you know everything.

346
00:12:03,960 --> 00:12:04,420
I'm off.

347
00:12:04,870 --> 00:12:05,910
Did I guess wrong?

348
00:12:07,320 --> 00:12:07,870
No way.

349
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:09,510
We're business partners now, right?

350
00:12:09,510 --> 00:12:11,360
Knowing you as I do...

351
00:12:13,240 --> 00:12:14,320
I guessed right, didn't I?

352
00:12:14,320 --> 00:12:15,120
I knew it.

353
00:12:16,030 --> 00:12:18,890
You really don't have anything else
to see me about?

354
00:12:19,270 --> 00:12:19,960
I do.

355
00:12:20,510 --> 00:12:21,480
Didn't you ask me before

356
00:12:21,480 --> 00:12:23,940
to help track down
the Yu family's antiques?

357
00:12:24,360 --> 00:12:25,360
I recently found a clue

358
00:12:25,360 --> 00:12:27,120
about that blue-and-white porcelain vase.

359
00:12:27,120 --> 00:12:28,120
Because it was brought to Gangdao

360
00:12:28,120 --> 00:12:28,920
from Shengcheng,

361
00:12:28,920 --> 00:12:30,200
it was relatively easy to trace.

362
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:30,670
Really?

363
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:31,770
So who has it now?

364
00:12:37,790 --> 00:12:39,120
You want shrimp, right?

365
00:12:39,150 --> 00:12:39,610
Come on.

366
00:12:40,080 --> 00:12:40,910
I'll peel it for you.

367
00:12:40,910 --> 00:12:41,310
Let me.

368
00:12:41,510 --> 00:12:42,440
No need, no need.

369
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:45,240
I've already tracked it down.

370
00:12:45,240 --> 00:12:47,640
It's in the hands of someone
called Mr. Qiu.

371
00:12:47,720 --> 00:12:48,320
He's an antique dealer

372
00:12:48,320 --> 00:12:49,630
in Gangdao,

373
00:12:50,270 --> 00:12:50,910
and

374
00:12:51,150 --> 00:12:52,830
a lot of black-market antiques there

375
00:12:52,830 --> 00:12:53,870
go through him.

376
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:55,910
I've managed to
make an appointment with him,

377
00:12:55,910 --> 00:12:57,710
but he's really hard to pin down.

378
00:12:58,270 --> 00:12:58,670
Okay.

379
00:12:59,140 --> 00:13:01,540
Then let me thank you
on behalf of Granny Yu.

380
00:13:01,840 --> 00:13:02,900
No need to thank me.

381
00:13:03,550 --> 00:13:04,870
We're...

382
00:13:07,870 --> 00:13:08,910
business partners.

383
00:13:08,910 --> 00:13:10,370
Remember that, partners.

384
00:13:10,440 --> 00:13:10,900
I'm off.

385
00:13:17,020 --> 00:13:18,730
[Qi Hang Property]

386
00:13:26,790 --> 00:13:28,840
So, did they approve it or not?

387
00:13:29,200 --> 00:13:30,360
Should we just call Xiaolan

388
00:13:30,360 --> 00:13:31,440
on her cell phone and ask?

389
00:13:31,440 --> 00:13:33,900
Sit down.
Pacing around isn't going to help.

390
00:13:35,730 --> 00:13:36,210
Mr. Mao,

391
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:37,200
how about we eat first?

392
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:38,150
The dishes are getting cold.

393
00:13:38,150 --> 00:13:39,840
Okay, let's eat while we wait.

394
00:13:39,860 --> 00:13:40,320
Come on.

395
00:13:45,240 --> 00:13:45,770
How is it?

396
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:47,930
Did the bank approve it?

397
00:13:51,480 --> 00:13:52,810
They didn't approve it?

398
00:13:57,030 --> 00:13:58,600
Say something.

399
00:13:58,630 --> 00:13:59,760
Did they approve it?

400
00:14:03,510 --> 00:14:04,080
The loan got approved!

401
00:14:04,080 --> 00:14:05,740
We have the money to build now!

402
00:14:07,360 --> 00:14:08,080
Great!

403
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:09,390
Wait, wait!

404
00:14:09,670 --> 00:14:11,120
How much did they approve?

405
00:14:11,120 --> 00:14:11,650
How much?

406
00:14:12,750 --> 00:14:15,240
Fifteen million!

407
00:14:15,840 --> 00:14:17,270
Oh my God.

408
00:14:17,290 --> 00:14:18,550
Less than three million

409
00:14:18,550 --> 00:14:20,680
turned into five times that in a month!

410
00:14:20,790 --> 00:14:21,630
I didn't expect

411
00:14:21,630 --> 00:14:22,790
they'd actually give us

412
00:14:22,790 --> 00:14:23,850
15 million either.

413
00:14:24,200 --> 00:14:25,240
Speaking of which,

414
00:14:25,240 --> 00:14:26,770
we have to thank Du Zhaohui.

415
00:14:27,270 --> 00:14:28,120
Let's raise a toast in Du Zhaohui's honor!

416
00:14:28,120 --> 00:14:28,600
Come on.

417
00:14:29,030 --> 00:14:29,480
Ms. Xia.

418
00:14:29,480 --> 00:14:31,030
Let's wish for good luck.

419
00:14:31,440 --> 00:14:33,770
Qi Hang, Qi Hang,
brave the wind and waves!

420
00:14:33,840 --> 00:14:35,480
-Let's shout the slogan.
-One, two, three!

421
00:14:35,480 --> 00:14:38,670
Qi Hang, Qi Hang,
brave the wind and waves!

422
00:14:38,690 --> 00:14:40,180
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

423
00:14:40,600 --> 00:14:41,870
What did the bank say?

424
00:14:43,030 --> 00:14:43,510
What?

425
00:14:44,600 --> 00:14:45,660
That's wonderful!

426
00:14:45,910 --> 00:14:46,440
Really?

427
00:14:46,910 --> 00:14:49,110
Okay, okay. I'll tell the Young Master.

428
00:14:50,320 --> 00:14:51,320
Young Master! Young Master!

429
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:52,520
Good news! Good news!

430
00:14:52,600 --> 00:14:53,480
Ms. Xia's loan

431
00:14:53,480 --> 00:14:54,540
has been approved.

432
00:14:55,030 --> 00:14:55,830
That's great!

433
00:14:56,390 --> 00:14:57,320
Where is she now?

434
00:14:57,360 --> 00:14:59,560
She's celebrating at Qi Hang right now.

435
00:14:59,960 --> 00:15:00,950
She didn't invite me?

436
00:15:00,950 --> 00:15:07,060
♪ Love has faded,
and so has the bond between us ♪

437
00:15:03,630 --> 00:15:04,230
Forget it.

438
00:15:04,550 --> 00:15:06,360
That Jerk Zhou is definitely there—

439
00:15:06,360 --> 00:15:07,300
I don't want to see him anyway.

440
00:15:07,300 --> 00:15:12,810
♪ Yet, why do I still love you? ♪

441
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:09,840
You two,

442
00:15:10,360 --> 00:15:11,020
get to work!

443
00:15:11,080 --> 00:15:12,280
Or I'll dock your pay.

444
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:14,720
You've got to admit, I'm awesome, right?

445
00:15:14,720 --> 00:15:16,440
Awesome. You're the best.

446
00:15:16,840 --> 00:15:17,320
From the very first day

447
00:15:17,320 --> 00:15:18,390
I met you,

448
00:15:18,390 --> 00:15:19,720
I knew you could make it.

449
00:15:20,150 --> 00:15:21,390
Put me down already.

450
00:15:22,960 --> 00:15:23,760
Stand steady.

451
00:15:25,910 --> 00:15:27,000
I think so too.

452
00:15:28,150 --> 00:15:29,280
Alright, go inside.

453
00:15:29,600 --> 00:15:30,440
Or Granny Yu

454
00:15:30,440 --> 00:15:32,100
will suddenly come out again.

455
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:33,720
Um...

456
00:15:34,390 --> 00:15:37,030
Jiang Yan will be discharged
in a couple of days.

457
00:15:37,030 --> 00:15:37,750
Really?

458
00:15:38,320 --> 00:15:39,120
That's great.

459
00:15:39,360 --> 00:15:40,200
How is her recovery?

460
00:15:40,200 --> 00:15:41,750
Does she still need follow-up checks?

461
00:15:41,750 --> 00:15:42,720
She'll probably still need

462
00:15:42,720 --> 00:15:43,850
regular check-ups.

463
00:15:44,270 --> 00:15:46,600
But her daily life shouldn't be a problem.

464
00:15:47,550 --> 00:15:49,150
Every time I think of

465
00:15:49,510 --> 00:15:50,570
what Jiang Yan has endured,

466
00:15:50,570 --> 00:15:52,300
I feel both sorry and grateful.

467
00:15:52,750 --> 00:15:53,810
She's a good person

468
00:15:54,030 --> 00:15:55,560
and an upright prosecutor.

469
00:15:57,030 --> 00:15:58,030
She truly

470
00:15:58,320 --> 00:16:01,050
deserves someone
who loves her wholeheartedly.

471
00:16:01,240 --> 00:16:01,670
Oh,

472
00:16:01,790 --> 00:16:04,840
she said after she's discharged,

473
00:16:05,510 --> 00:16:06,840
she wants to have a meal with both of us.

474
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:07,750
Is that okay?

475
00:16:08,030 --> 00:16:08,750
Of course.

476
00:16:10,440 --> 00:16:12,170
Okay, you should head back now.

477
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:13,240
I'll watch you go in.

478
00:16:13,240 --> 00:16:14,030
What's there to see?

479
00:16:14,030 --> 00:16:15,030
You see it every day. Go.

480
00:16:15,030 --> 00:16:17,670
-What if something happens to you?
-Go already!

481
00:16:17,670 --> 00:16:18,200
Bye-bye!

482
00:16:19,240 --> 00:16:19,700
I'm off.

483
00:16:31,670 --> 00:16:32,270
Granny Yu.

484
00:16:33,000 --> 00:16:35,000
It's so late. Aren't you asleep yet?

485
00:16:35,720 --> 00:16:36,240
Not yet.

486
00:16:37,910 --> 00:16:38,960
If I were asleep,

487
00:16:39,270 --> 00:16:40,360
how could I have heard

488
00:16:40,360 --> 00:16:42,560
you two talking about me behind my back?

489
00:16:43,910 --> 00:16:45,200
You young people

490
00:16:45,480 --> 00:16:46,750
always think

491
00:16:47,270 --> 00:16:48,390
work is the most important thing,

492
00:16:48,390 --> 00:16:49,790
that a career comes above all else.

493
00:16:49,790 --> 00:16:50,590
But honestly,

494
00:16:51,080 --> 00:16:52,630
when you reach my age,

495
00:16:52,840 --> 00:16:54,080
you'll understand

496
00:16:54,720 --> 00:16:56,520
that the most important thing is

497
00:16:57,270 --> 00:16:59,070
keeping the people close to you.

498
00:17:00,510 --> 00:17:01,630
I'll stop rambling now,

499
00:17:01,630 --> 00:17:03,910
or I'll just annoy you.

500
00:17:04,640 --> 00:17:05,900
Goodnight, Granny Yu.

501
00:17:06,109 --> 00:17:06,770
Goodnight!

502
00:17:09,349 --> 00:17:10,550
I want to keep him too.

503
00:17:11,069 --> 00:17:12,109
There are still too many things

504
00:17:12,109 --> 00:17:13,240
I haven't finished.

505
00:17:14,200 --> 00:17:15,720
I hope the day I wake from this dream

506
00:17:15,720 --> 00:17:16,920
comes a little later—

507
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:18,130
just a little later.

508
00:17:18,480 --> 00:17:20,680
I want to see Liu Fen find happiness.

509
00:17:21,200 --> 00:17:23,400
I want to help Granny Yu find her family.

510
00:17:23,640 --> 00:17:25,520
I also want to see
the Golden Sands Pool project completed,

511
00:17:25,520 --> 00:17:28,000
even if only in the dream.

512
00:17:32,270 --> 00:17:32,730
Ms. Xia.

513
00:17:32,880 --> 00:17:33,480
Mr. Mao.

514
00:17:34,070 --> 00:17:35,720
The terrain of this lake is quite complex.

515
00:17:35,720 --> 00:17:37,240
We've cleared the surrounding weeds

516
00:17:37,240 --> 00:17:38,510
and silt.

517
00:17:38,830 --> 00:17:40,490
We're ready for the next plan.

518
00:17:41,070 --> 00:17:42,790
If we build,
we must build high-quality buildings.

519
00:17:42,790 --> 00:17:44,270
Otherwise, it would be a disservice

520
00:17:44,270 --> 00:17:45,880
to Golden Sands Pool's current fame.

521
00:17:45,880 --> 00:17:47,200
I imagine the buyers who come

522
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:48,880
attracted by the legend of
this gold-bearing land

523
00:17:48,880 --> 00:17:50,440
wouldn't want to see

524
00:17:50,460 --> 00:17:51,240
just an ordinary concrete block

525
00:17:51,240 --> 00:17:52,270
going up here.

526
00:17:52,590 --> 00:17:53,070
Ms. Xia,

527
00:17:53,510 --> 00:17:55,160
the Golden Sands Pool is quite large.

528
00:17:55,160 --> 00:17:57,090
We'd lose space for so many houses.

529
00:17:59,110 --> 00:18:00,330
The pool must be preserved,

530
00:18:00,330 --> 00:18:02,130
but we must shrink the area

531
00:18:02,160 --> 00:18:03,510
to about one mu.

532
00:18:04,030 --> 00:18:06,440
In the center,
we'll build a courtyard landscape.

533
00:18:06,440 --> 00:18:07,160
That way,

534
00:18:07,510 --> 00:18:09,270
on the left, you have the golf course;

535
00:18:09,270 --> 00:18:11,200
on the right, Qingyue Lake;

536
00:18:11,480 --> 00:18:13,740
and in the middle, the courtyard garden.

537
00:18:13,790 --> 00:18:15,400
No matter which angle you look from,

538
00:18:15,400 --> 00:18:16,790
the scenery will be excellent—

539
00:18:16,790 --> 00:18:17,720
very appealing.

540
00:18:18,070 --> 00:18:19,920
Yes, we sacrifice some floor area,

541
00:18:19,920 --> 00:18:20,790
but in return, we get

542
00:18:20,790 --> 00:18:22,920
the best possible living experience.

543
00:18:24,240 --> 00:18:26,110
Sounds like
you've genuinely planned this out.

544
00:18:26,110 --> 00:18:27,110
I thought

545
00:18:27,110 --> 00:18:29,110
you were so focused on being the boss

546
00:18:29,110 --> 00:18:30,160
that you'd dump the architectural design

547
00:18:30,160 --> 00:18:31,310
on someone else.

548
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:33,720
Mr. Mao, you're joking.

549
00:18:33,750 --> 00:18:35,400
My fellow classmates and peers

550
00:18:35,400 --> 00:18:37,200
have spent their entire careers
drawing blueprints,

551
00:18:37,200 --> 00:18:38,350
but very few ever see

552
00:18:38,350 --> 00:18:40,240
their designs become real buildings.

553
00:18:40,240 --> 00:18:41,920
I run my own company now.
If I don't do the design myself,

554
00:18:41,920 --> 00:18:43,310
am I really supposed to wait

555
00:18:43,310 --> 00:18:44,480
for someone else to hire

556
00:18:44,480 --> 00:18:45,410
a rookie like me?

557
00:18:45,550 --> 00:18:46,240
Besides,

558
00:18:46,510 --> 00:18:47,960
I wouldn't want to miss the opportunity

559
00:18:47,960 --> 00:18:49,110
to have a mentor

560
00:18:49,110 --> 00:18:50,510
as good as you guiding me.

561
00:18:51,090 --> 00:18:52,130
Y-You girl...

562
00:18:52,510 --> 00:18:54,710
you're getting smooth with your words.

563
00:19:04,110 --> 00:19:04,830
Great.

564
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:06,920
At least you haven't forgotten

565
00:19:06,920 --> 00:19:07,440
that your true calling

566
00:19:07,440 --> 00:19:09,000
is architectural design.

567
00:19:09,480 --> 00:19:10,110
Xiaolan,

568
00:19:10,640 --> 00:19:12,240
I have something to tell you.

569
00:19:12,310 --> 00:19:14,200
I've recommended you

570
00:19:14,200 --> 00:19:15,640
for the Jiangcheng Architecture Symposium

571
00:19:15,640 --> 00:19:17,970
based on your design for the Haihua Hotel.

572
00:19:18,360 --> 00:19:19,070
When you're there,

573
00:19:19,070 --> 00:19:20,310
you must seize the opportunity

574
00:19:20,310 --> 00:19:21,880
to network with your peers.

575
00:19:22,350 --> 00:19:23,350
While we're at it,

576
00:19:23,510 --> 00:19:25,480
I'll take you to make your debut—

577
00:19:26,590 --> 00:19:27,590
let everyone see you,

578
00:19:27,590 --> 00:19:28,790
my new apprentice.

579
00:19:29,350 --> 00:19:29,750
Okay.

580
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:31,060
Thank you, Mr. Mao.

581
00:19:31,440 --> 00:19:33,300
I've already thought it through.

582
00:19:33,310 --> 00:19:34,960
We're going to build

583
00:19:34,960 --> 00:19:36,720
a building with one elevator
shared between two units,

584
00:19:36,720 --> 00:19:37,920
five floors in total.

585
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:40,070
Each first-floor unit comes with a garage

586
00:19:40,070 --> 00:19:41,200
in the basement.

587
00:19:41,510 --> 00:19:42,110
As for the top floor,

588
00:19:42,110 --> 00:19:43,570
we'll build a roof garden.

589
00:19:43,590 --> 00:19:44,350
The floors below the top

590
00:19:44,350 --> 00:19:45,680
will be standard units,

591
00:19:45,880 --> 00:19:46,550
and the top floor can

592
00:19:46,550 --> 00:19:47,810
also have a small loft,

593
00:19:47,880 --> 00:19:49,640
making it a duplex penthouse.

594
00:19:50,920 --> 00:19:51,920
If we do this,

595
00:19:52,110 --> 00:19:53,750
we'll be building many fewer units.

596
00:19:53,750 --> 00:19:54,960
Can we really make money?

597
00:19:54,960 --> 00:19:56,350
Whether it's profitable

598
00:19:56,350 --> 00:19:57,440
depends on

599
00:19:57,440 --> 00:19:59,170
what price we sell the units at.

600
00:19:59,210 --> 00:20:01,070
I think Xiaolan's overall vision

601
00:20:01,070 --> 00:20:02,070
is very clear.

602
00:20:02,440 --> 00:20:02,970
Xiaolan,

603
00:20:03,240 --> 00:20:04,200
go ahead boldly.

604
00:20:04,830 --> 00:20:05,200
Okay.

605
00:20:05,440 --> 00:20:06,640
I'll draw the designs

606
00:20:06,640 --> 00:20:07,310
and show you.

607
00:20:07,310 --> 00:20:07,970
Okay, okay.

608
00:20:08,030 --> 00:20:09,560
Man, this is a construction site!

609
00:20:09,560 --> 00:20:10,880
You can't come in without permission!

610
00:20:10,880 --> 00:20:12,140
Don't come here again!

611
00:20:12,240 --> 00:20:12,830
Don't come back!

612
00:20:12,830 --> 00:20:14,070
Look how dangerous this is!

613
00:20:14,070 --> 00:20:15,000
Go back! Go back!

614
00:20:15,110 --> 00:20:16,040
Don't come back!

615
00:20:16,400 --> 00:20:17,330
Go back, go back.

616
00:20:17,440 --> 00:20:18,680
Break it up. Go back, everyone.

617
00:20:18,680 --> 00:20:19,160
Go back.

618
00:20:19,920 --> 00:20:20,920
What are you doing?

619
00:20:20,920 --> 00:20:21,270
Stop!

620
00:20:21,270 --> 00:20:22,200
Okay, okay.

621
00:20:22,350 --> 00:20:23,480
Stop playing! Stop!

622
00:20:23,640 --> 00:20:24,310
Officer,

623
00:20:24,590 --> 00:20:25,540
we're not here to cause trouble.

624
00:20:25,540 --> 00:20:26,110
You see,

625
00:20:26,110 --> 00:20:27,480
gold was found here, wasn't it?

626
00:20:27,480 --> 00:20:28,480
My grandpa is old.

627
00:20:28,510 --> 00:20:29,350
When he heard the news,

628
00:20:29,350 --> 00:20:30,270
he couldn't take the shock

629
00:20:30,270 --> 00:20:31,310
and collapsed right then.

630
00:20:31,310 --> 00:20:32,350
Look at his condition—

631
00:20:32,350 --> 00:20:33,720
he's getting worse day by day.

632
00:20:33,720 --> 00:20:34,480
He just wants to go in

633
00:20:34,480 --> 00:20:35,590
and take one last look.

634
00:20:35,590 --> 00:20:37,510
Otherwise, he won't rest in peace.

635
00:20:37,510 --> 00:20:38,170
Who are you?

636
00:20:38,730 --> 00:20:39,730
I'm his grandson.

637
00:20:41,010 --> 00:20:41,920
This is their construction site.

638
00:20:41,920 --> 00:20:43,240
They have every right to develop it.

639
00:20:43,240 --> 00:20:44,240
You show up here every day
with all these people...

640
00:20:44,240 --> 00:20:44,880
Mr. Ge Jian,

641
00:20:44,880 --> 00:20:45,550
Ms. Xia is looking for you.

642
00:20:45,550 --> 00:20:46,640
You should be grateful they didn't

643
00:20:46,640 --> 00:20:47,480
hold you responsible.

644
00:20:47,480 --> 00:20:48,240
Disperse now.

645
00:20:48,240 --> 00:20:49,530
Take your people and go back.

646
00:20:49,530 --> 00:20:50,680
We're not causing any trouble.

647
00:20:50,680 --> 00:20:52,000
And we won't get in the way
of her digging for gold.

648
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:53,600
We just want to go in and look.

649
00:20:58,000 --> 00:20:58,480
Ms. Xia.

650
00:20:59,070 --> 00:21:00,200
You wanted to see me?

651
00:21:01,160 --> 00:21:02,760
The Luo family is here again?

652
00:21:03,550 --> 00:21:04,790
These past few days, that Luo guy

653
00:21:04,790 --> 00:21:06,000
has been coming every day,

654
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:07,030
insisting on seeing you.

655
00:21:07,030 --> 00:21:07,880
Today, knowing you're here,

656
00:21:07,880 --> 00:21:08,640
he even

657
00:21:08,640 --> 00:21:10,070
had his grandfather carried over,

658
00:21:10,070 --> 00:21:12,000
worried that you wouldn't show up.

659
00:21:12,650 --> 00:21:14,170
He sees the dump

660
00:21:14,200 --> 00:21:15,440
has turned into a treasure land

661
00:21:15,440 --> 00:21:16,440
and wants in on it.

662
00:21:17,070 --> 00:21:18,550
Tell him to have the others leave,

663
00:21:18,550 --> 00:21:19,880
and I'll agree to meet him and his family.

664
00:21:19,880 --> 00:21:20,240
Okay.

665
00:21:36,110 --> 00:21:37,030
Easy, easy.

666
00:21:40,750 --> 00:21:42,210
Former Village Chief Luo,

667
00:21:42,480 --> 00:21:43,860
I only agreed to see you

668
00:21:44,160 --> 00:21:44,720
out of respect

669
00:21:44,720 --> 00:21:46,030
for your age.

670
00:21:46,550 --> 00:21:48,510
Don't bring up
anything about land rights with me.

671
00:21:48,510 --> 00:21:50,720
I bought this plot legally and properly.

672
00:21:50,720 --> 00:21:51,790
You know perfectly well yourself

673
00:21:51,790 --> 00:21:53,720
whether you're in the right or not.

674
00:21:53,830 --> 00:21:55,270
Fine, fine.

675
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:57,750
You've got guts, young lady.

676
00:21:58,510 --> 00:21:59,830
You stole my family's

677
00:21:59,830 --> 00:22:01,200
feng shui treasure land.

678
00:22:01,200 --> 00:22:02,600
We can't just let this go.

679
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:04,460
You have to compensate us.

680
00:22:05,350 --> 00:22:06,880
I don't owe your family anything.

681
00:22:06,880 --> 00:22:08,480
Why should I compensate you?

682
00:22:08,590 --> 00:22:10,390
Or are you trying to threaten me?

683
00:22:10,440 --> 00:22:11,720
That won't work on me.

684
00:22:12,480 --> 00:22:14,270
You can ask your grandson
if you don't believe me.

685
00:22:14,270 --> 00:22:14,750
Fine.

686
00:22:15,510 --> 00:22:17,370
Since you mentioned my grandson,

687
00:22:17,450 --> 00:22:18,440
then arrange a job for him

688
00:22:18,440 --> 00:22:19,590
at your company.

689
00:22:20,350 --> 00:22:21,920
Make him a manager or something.

690
00:22:21,920 --> 00:22:23,650
Manager is out of the question.

691
00:22:23,720 --> 00:22:25,480
But I'm still hiring security guards.

692
00:22:25,480 --> 00:22:26,210
Want the job?

693
00:22:27,030 --> 00:22:28,750
You're making Yaozong a security guard?

694
00:22:28,750 --> 00:22:30,110
You're looking down on us too much!

695
00:22:30,110 --> 00:22:30,720
Yeah!

696
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:32,000
Yaozong is the only male heir

697
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:32,790
of the Luo family for three generations!

698
00:22:32,790 --> 00:22:34,640
How can you run things this way,
little girl?

699
00:22:34,640 --> 00:22:35,070
Fine.

700
00:22:35,670 --> 00:22:36,440
Think it over and come back

701
00:22:36,440 --> 00:22:37,900
to me when you've decided.

702
00:22:38,400 --> 00:22:39,440
Wait, wait, wait!

703
00:22:43,640 --> 00:22:45,790
There's no justice in this world!

704
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:47,310
Our Luo family

705
00:22:47,310 --> 00:22:49,070
has done good deeds all our lives,

706
00:22:49,070 --> 00:22:51,270
but how did we end up like this?

707
00:22:52,070 --> 00:22:53,750
We treated Golden Sands Pool

708
00:22:53,750 --> 00:22:54,810
as a treasure land,

709
00:22:55,030 --> 00:22:55,920
not because of

710
00:22:55,920 --> 00:22:57,200
any gold here.

711
00:22:58,750 --> 00:22:59,790
Over 20 years ago,

712
00:22:59,790 --> 00:23:01,160
I saved someone here.

713
00:23:01,630 --> 00:23:02,830
That's the true source

714
00:23:02,830 --> 00:23:04,290
of our family's blessing.

715
00:23:04,920 --> 00:23:06,120
When did that happen?

716
00:23:06,510 --> 00:23:08,240
That was over 20 years ago.

717
00:23:09,830 --> 00:23:11,240
I remember one night...

718
00:23:11,590 --> 00:23:16,880
I, the old servant, was in a rush.

719
00:23:17,790 --> 00:23:19,750
I stepped forward

720
00:23:20,030 --> 00:23:22,200
and knelt down quickly.

721
00:23:34,920 --> 00:23:37,520
Gold-bearing sand
springing from the ground!

722
00:23:37,590 --> 00:23:40,190
Gold-bearing sand
springing from the ground!

723
00:23:57,030 --> 00:23:57,960
You're in luck.

724
00:23:58,720 --> 00:23:59,550
Fortunately,

725
00:24:00,270 --> 00:24:01,400
it's me you ran into.

726
00:24:03,070 --> 00:24:05,160
That person stayed at our home
for a couple of days,

727
00:24:05,160 --> 00:24:06,560
then left without a word.

728
00:24:07,200 --> 00:24:09,070
About half a year later,

729
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:11,400
someone left a wooden box

730
00:24:11,720 --> 00:24:12,790
at our house.

731
00:24:13,240 --> 00:24:14,170
When I opened it,

732
00:24:14,270 --> 00:24:16,070
there was an antique porcelain vase

733
00:24:16,070 --> 00:24:17,200
along with a letter.

734
00:24:17,590 --> 00:24:19,400
The letter was signed

735
00:24:20,110 --> 00:24:21,310
by a man surnamed Qiu.

736
00:24:21,920 --> 00:24:22,550
Qiu...

737
00:24:22,960 --> 00:24:24,070
I've already tracked it down.

738
00:24:24,070 --> 00:24:25,760
It's in the hands of someone
called Mr. Qiu.

739
00:24:25,760 --> 00:24:26,350
He's an antique dealer

740
00:24:26,350 --> 00:24:27,240
in Gangdao,

741
00:24:28,160 --> 00:24:29,750
and a lot of black-market antiques there

742
00:24:29,750 --> 00:24:30,720
go through him.

743
00:24:31,590 --> 00:24:32,550
An antique vase?

744
00:24:33,880 --> 00:24:35,440
Could it really be that coincidental?

745
00:24:35,440 --> 00:24:36,440
Do you remember

746
00:24:36,860 --> 00:24:38,190
how old

747
00:24:38,310 --> 00:24:39,200
that man was?

748
00:24:39,590 --> 00:24:40,720
What he looked like?

749
00:24:40,880 --> 00:24:42,940
Where are the vase and the letter now?

750
00:24:46,030 --> 00:24:46,890
I feel dizzy...

751
00:24:47,960 --> 00:24:48,820
I feel dizzy...

752
00:24:49,200 --> 00:24:50,730
I can't remember right now.

753
00:24:51,230 --> 00:24:51,830
Unless...

754
00:24:51,880 --> 00:24:53,400
Unless you make my grandson

755
00:24:53,400 --> 00:24:54,000
a manager.

756
00:24:55,640 --> 00:24:56,440
Listen up,

757
00:24:57,110 --> 00:24:58,960
I can be persuaded but not threatened.

758
00:24:58,960 --> 00:25:00,750
Luo Yaozong can only be a security guard.

759
00:25:00,750 --> 00:25:01,580
Take it or leave it.

760
00:25:01,580 --> 00:25:02,790
If he doesn't want it, forget it.

761
00:25:02,790 --> 00:25:03,310
That piece of information

762
00:25:03,310 --> 00:25:05,000
is valuable to me now,

763
00:25:05,360 --> 00:25:07,920
but that doesn't mean
it will still be valuable in a few days.

764
00:25:07,920 --> 00:25:08,750
From what I can see,

765
00:25:08,750 --> 00:25:09,350
Gancun Village isn't exactly a place

766
00:25:09,350 --> 00:25:10,610
that can hide secrets.

767
00:25:11,000 --> 00:25:13,060
It shouldn't be hard to investigate.

768
00:25:13,920 --> 00:25:14,440
Fine.

769
00:25:16,110 --> 00:25:17,400
I've never seen

770
00:25:17,400 --> 00:25:18,730
a woman as brazen as you.

771
00:25:19,480 --> 00:25:21,280
I didn't say I wouldn't tell you.

772
00:25:21,510 --> 00:25:22,680
But you're not offering us

773
00:25:22,680 --> 00:25:23,810
anything in return.

774
00:25:24,350 --> 00:25:25,080
Is that fair?

775
00:25:25,480 --> 00:25:26,010
Grandpa,

776
00:25:26,310 --> 00:25:27,550
I don't want to be a security guard.

777
00:25:27,550 --> 00:25:28,510
What do you know?

778
00:25:30,240 --> 00:25:31,400
Have you made a decision?

779
00:25:31,400 --> 00:25:32,720
If you won't say it, I'm leaving.

780
00:25:32,720 --> 00:25:33,380
Wait, wait.

781
00:25:34,160 --> 00:25:35,220
Alright, alright.

782
00:25:36,240 --> 00:25:38,070
Yaozong will take the position.

783
00:25:39,240 --> 00:25:40,370
If he does a good job,

784
00:25:40,790 --> 00:25:42,000
he can be promoted to manager, right?

785
00:25:42,000 --> 00:25:42,600
Of course.

786
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:44,200
As long as you work hard,

787
00:25:44,200 --> 00:25:46,240
everyone has a chance for promotion.

788
00:25:46,240 --> 00:25:47,440
It all depends on him.

789
00:25:48,880 --> 00:25:49,560
Alright then,

790
00:25:49,560 --> 00:25:50,360
I'll tell you.

791
00:25:51,600 --> 00:25:53,510
It was a blue-and-white porcelain vase.

792
00:25:53,510 --> 00:25:54,440
About this high,

793
00:25:55,400 --> 00:25:56,830
with an opening this wide.

794
00:25:56,830 --> 00:25:57,470
And the letter

795
00:25:57,470 --> 00:25:58,670
was tucked inside it.

796
00:25:58,880 --> 00:25:59,680
As for the man,

797
00:26:00,200 --> 00:26:02,260
he was probably in his mid-twenties.

798
00:26:02,460 --> 00:26:03,460
His height...

799
00:26:05,070 --> 00:26:06,830
was about the same as our Yaozong.

800
00:26:06,830 --> 00:26:08,750
He had a cut on his forehead at the time,

801
00:26:08,750 --> 00:26:09,160
so I

802
00:26:09,160 --> 00:26:11,110
didn't dare look at his face directly.

803
00:26:11,110 --> 00:26:12,920
Although his clothes were dirty,

804
00:26:12,920 --> 00:26:14,880
I could tell he came from
a well-off family.

805
00:26:14,880 --> 00:26:17,000
As for the letter,
I can't find it anymore.

806
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:19,550
I remember he told me at the time

807
00:26:20,030 --> 00:26:21,690
that he ran into some enemies.

808
00:26:22,160 --> 00:26:23,720
Could he be Granny Yu's son?

809
00:26:24,550 --> 00:26:25,510
What exactly

810
00:26:25,510 --> 00:26:26,910
happened to him back then

811
00:26:27,200 --> 00:26:28,400
that caused such serious injuries?

812
00:26:28,400 --> 00:26:29,440
That's all

813
00:26:29,460 --> 00:26:30,260
I can tell you.

814
00:26:30,890 --> 00:26:32,620
I definitely didn't lie to you.

815
00:26:33,960 --> 00:26:34,920
Whether you lied or not,

816
00:26:34,920 --> 00:26:35,880
I'll find out.

817
00:26:36,830 --> 00:26:37,360
Alright.

818
00:26:37,750 --> 00:26:38,680
You start

819
00:26:38,680 --> 00:26:39,940
officially tomorrow.

820
00:26:40,110 --> 00:26:40,830
From now on, you're

821
00:26:40,830 --> 00:26:42,480
a security guard
at this construction site.

822
00:26:42,480 --> 00:26:44,060
If anyone causes trouble again,

823
00:26:44,060 --> 00:26:45,260
just drive them away.

824
00:26:47,160 --> 00:26:47,830
Mr. Luo,

825
00:26:48,430 --> 00:26:49,430
Ms. Xia has agreed

826
00:26:49,440 --> 00:26:50,680
to your request.

827
00:26:51,310 --> 00:26:52,880
Yaozong will come to work
at the site tomorrow.

828
00:26:52,880 --> 00:26:53,720
At your age,

829
00:26:53,720 --> 00:26:54,640
please don't make a fuss anymore.

830
00:26:54,640 --> 00:26:55,510
Come on, come on!

831
00:26:55,510 --> 00:26:57,240
Get on. Let them wheel you back.

832
00:26:59,070 --> 00:27:00,130
Careful, careful!

833
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:02,440
Okay.

834
00:27:02,690 --> 00:27:03,220
Yaozong,

835
00:27:03,480 --> 00:27:04,240
since you're coming to work tomorrow,

836
00:27:04,240 --> 00:27:05,510
no more causing trouble!

837
00:27:05,510 --> 00:27:06,550
It's your job to keep an eye on them now.

838
00:27:06,550 --> 00:27:07,030
Go back!

839
00:27:14,830 --> 00:27:15,510
Look at

840
00:27:15,510 --> 00:27:16,320
this workplace of yours,

841
00:27:16,320 --> 00:27:18,600
[Zhiyuan Law Firm]

842
00:27:16,640 --> 00:27:18,040
it's so small and shabby.

843
00:27:18,350 --> 00:27:20,210
It doesn't even look legitimate.

844
00:27:20,590 --> 00:27:21,590
You,

845
00:27:21,790 --> 00:27:23,160
a Huaqing Law School graduate,

846
00:27:23,160 --> 00:27:23,960
why did you join

847
00:27:23,960 --> 00:27:24,830
a private law firm

848
00:27:24,830 --> 00:27:25,750
like this?

849
00:27:26,320 --> 00:27:27,110
Think about it—

850
00:27:27,110 --> 00:27:28,400
if you could work at the procuratorate,

851
00:27:28,400 --> 00:27:29,190
how great would that be?

852
00:27:29,190 --> 00:27:30,680
You'd be in the same unit as my daughter.

853
00:27:30,680 --> 00:27:32,430
If you two get married in the future,

854
00:27:32,430 --> 00:27:33,400
wouldn't it be easier and faster

855
00:27:33,400 --> 00:27:34,350
to get an apartment allocated?

856
00:27:34,350 --> 00:27:35,230
You'll be a dual-income household!

857
00:27:35,230 --> 00:27:35,750
Auntie.

858
00:27:36,920 --> 00:27:37,880
You're an elder

859
00:27:37,880 --> 00:27:39,140
who watched me grow up.

860
00:27:39,560 --> 00:27:40,890
I respect you very much.

861
00:27:41,570 --> 00:27:43,370
But I hope you can respect me too.

862
00:27:43,400 --> 00:27:45,660
Jiang Yan and I are not in a relationship.

863
00:27:46,000 --> 00:27:47,480
I already have a girlfriend.

864
00:27:47,480 --> 00:27:49,790
You can't just go on like that
without considering others.

865
00:27:49,790 --> 00:27:51,000
As for my job

866
00:27:51,640 --> 00:27:52,570
and my future...

867
00:27:54,180 --> 00:27:55,980
you don't need to worry about it.

868
00:27:56,030 --> 00:27:57,520
How can you say that?

869
00:27:57,540 --> 00:27:58,130
I...

870
00:28:02,230 --> 00:28:03,930
[Xia Xiaolan paging: Meet me at Qi Hang.]

871
00:28:11,110 --> 00:28:11,570
Auntie.

872
00:28:12,640 --> 00:28:14,040
If there's nothing else,

873
00:28:15,070 --> 00:28:16,000
I'll see you out.

874
00:28:16,750 --> 00:28:17,160
You...

875
00:28:18,830 --> 00:28:20,630
Don't bother. I'll go by myself.

876
00:28:20,880 --> 00:28:22,340
I'll come again next time.

877
00:28:24,730 --> 00:28:28,690
[Qi Hang Property]

878
00:28:26,110 --> 00:28:26,680
So,

879
00:28:26,880 --> 00:28:28,880
I have to go to Gangdao immediately.

880
00:28:28,990 --> 00:28:30,110
But what Former Village Chief Luo said

881
00:28:30,110 --> 00:28:31,570
really sounds like a trap.

882
00:28:32,510 --> 00:28:34,510
I also think it's probably no coincidence

883
00:28:34,510 --> 00:28:36,590
that he suddenly brought up something

884
00:28:36,590 --> 00:28:38,160
from over 20 years ago today.

885
00:28:38,160 --> 00:28:39,760
But whether it's true or not,

886
00:28:39,790 --> 00:28:40,270
it's rare to have

887
00:28:40,270 --> 00:28:41,590
a lead about Granny Yu's family.

888
00:28:41,590 --> 00:28:42,510
I must go.

889
00:28:44,550 --> 00:28:44,920
Okay.

890
00:28:45,680 --> 00:28:46,940
I'll go with you, then.

891
00:28:47,030 --> 00:28:47,830
No, you can't.

892
00:28:48,190 --> 00:28:49,820
Weren't you suspecting this

893
00:28:49,880 --> 00:28:51,440
might be connected to that smuggling case?

894
00:28:51,440 --> 00:28:52,960
You and Jiang Yan just had that incident.

895
00:28:52,960 --> 00:28:54,560
If you show up in Gangdao now,

896
00:28:54,680 --> 00:28:55,790
wouldn't it be easier for those

897
00:28:55,790 --> 00:28:56,880
who want to hurt you to make a move?

898
00:28:56,880 --> 00:28:58,000
But I wanted to...

899
00:28:58,000 --> 00:28:58,830
Alright.

900
00:28:59,790 --> 00:29:00,520
Don't worry.

901
00:29:01,000 --> 00:29:02,790
Jiang Yan will be discharged soon.

902
00:29:02,790 --> 00:29:04,450
Stay and take good care of her first.

903
00:29:04,450 --> 00:29:05,440
I'll ask Du Zhaohui

904
00:29:05,440 --> 00:29:06,700
to handle my security.

905
00:29:06,880 --> 00:29:08,720
As a guest of the Du family in Gangdao,

906
00:29:08,720 --> 00:29:10,650
no one would dare to lay a hand on me.

907
00:29:11,880 --> 00:29:12,590
Once I get

908
00:29:12,590 --> 00:29:14,070
news about Granny Yu's family,

909
00:29:14,070 --> 00:29:15,470
I'll come straight back.

910
00:29:15,550 --> 00:29:16,070
Okay?

911
00:29:36,750 --> 00:29:37,150
Hello?

912
00:29:39,550 --> 00:29:40,350
I told her.

913
00:29:41,110 --> 00:29:43,170
I told her everything about the past.

914
00:29:45,840 --> 00:29:50,020
[Gangdao]

915
00:29:52,640 --> 00:29:53,510
Now that you're in Gangdao,

916
00:29:53,510 --> 00:29:54,720
you're on my turf.

917
00:29:55,110 --> 00:29:55,550
Relax.

918
00:29:55,790 --> 00:29:56,650
You'll be safe.

919
00:29:58,160 --> 00:30:00,510
Don't you think
that at a critical moment like this,

920
00:30:00,510 --> 00:30:01,400
I'm far more useful

921
00:30:01,400 --> 00:30:02,530
than that Jerk Zhou?

922
00:30:04,680 --> 00:30:05,640
Besides meeting Mr. Qiu,

923
00:30:05,640 --> 00:30:06,920
I need another favor.

924
00:30:07,960 --> 00:30:09,500
Help me find a property consultant

925
00:30:09,500 --> 00:30:11,110
to come check out Golden Sands Pool.

926
00:30:11,110 --> 00:30:12,350
It's also a good opportunity

927
00:30:12,350 --> 00:30:13,370
to let the Gangdao merchants
going to Shengcheng

928
00:30:13,370 --> 00:30:15,370
know about this gold-bearing land.

929
00:30:15,590 --> 00:30:16,350
I knew it.

930
00:30:16,830 --> 00:30:19,110
You came here
just to make money off our money.

931
00:30:19,110 --> 00:30:19,510
What?

932
00:30:20,160 --> 00:30:21,550
You Gangdao merchants are allowed

933
00:30:21,550 --> 00:30:22,750
to make money in Shengcheng,

934
00:30:22,750 --> 00:30:24,350
but we can't earn your money?

935
00:30:25,000 --> 00:30:25,830
Alright, alright.

936
00:30:25,830 --> 00:30:26,440
You win.

937
00:30:27,750 --> 00:30:28,680
Y-Young Master.

938
00:30:28,960 --> 00:30:30,160
There seems to be a car

939
00:30:30,160 --> 00:30:31,620
that's been following us.

940
00:30:36,890 --> 00:30:38,550
Young Master Du, didn't you say

941
00:30:38,550 --> 00:30:40,680
Gangdao was the safest place
with you around?

942
00:30:40,680 --> 00:30:41,310
Darn it.

943
00:30:42,160 --> 00:30:43,510
Who dares to tail me?

944
00:30:45,510 --> 00:30:46,110
Pull over.

945
00:31:04,070 --> 00:31:04,600
Let's go.

946
00:31:05,470 --> 00:31:05,920
Okay.

947
00:31:12,830 --> 00:31:13,960
They've spotted us.

948
00:31:14,480 --> 00:31:15,740
Did you get a good look?

949
00:31:16,550 --> 00:31:17,150
Yes, I did.

950
00:31:17,310 --> 00:31:17,840
It's her.

951
00:31:18,750 --> 00:31:19,160
Good.

952
00:31:19,700 --> 00:31:20,420
No need to follow anymore.

953
00:31:20,420 --> 00:31:21,680
-All done.
-Thank you.

954
00:31:22,550 --> 00:31:23,080
Let's go.

955
00:31:24,030 --> 00:31:24,510
Next.

956
00:31:24,750 --> 00:31:25,200
Mom?

957
00:31:25,680 --> 00:31:27,010
What are you doing here?

958
00:31:27,720 --> 00:31:29,270
What do you mean by that?

959
00:31:29,590 --> 00:31:30,550
Are you planning to

960
00:31:30,550 --> 00:31:32,480
leave the hospital just like that?

961
00:31:32,680 --> 00:31:33,550
Once my daughter is discharged,

962
00:31:33,550 --> 00:31:35,750
you think this whole thing is just over?

963
00:31:36,110 --> 00:31:36,590
Auntie,

964
00:31:37,310 --> 00:31:38,710
I never meant it that way.

965
00:31:39,000 --> 00:31:40,680
I won't ignore Jiang Yan's situation.

966
00:31:40,680 --> 00:31:42,160
But definitely not in the way

967
00:31:42,160 --> 00:31:43,240
you're thinking.

968
00:31:44,210 --> 00:31:45,200
Zhou Cheng, if that's your attitude,

969
00:31:45,200 --> 00:31:46,240
I'll go straight to your superiors,

970
00:31:46,240 --> 00:31:46,880
your parents,

971
00:31:46,880 --> 00:31:47,940
your whole family.

972
00:31:48,440 --> 00:31:49,070
If you feel

973
00:31:49,070 --> 00:31:50,440
you absolutely must do that,

974
00:31:50,440 --> 00:31:51,240
then go ahead.

975
00:31:51,830 --> 00:31:52,350
Do you think

976
00:31:52,350 --> 00:31:53,480
-I won't dare?
-Mom!

977
00:31:53,790 --> 00:31:54,920
Enough. Stop it.

978
00:31:55,680 --> 00:31:57,350
You're not making things hard
for Zhou Cheng—

979
00:31:57,350 --> 00:31:59,110
you're making things hard for me!

980
00:31:59,110 --> 00:32:00,570
Am I really that unworthy?

981
00:32:00,680 --> 00:32:01,350
Do I really need to use an accident

982
00:32:01,350 --> 00:32:02,790
to guilt-trip someone into being with me?

983
00:32:02,790 --> 00:32:04,030
What do you mean by "guilt-trip"?

984
00:32:04,030 --> 00:32:05,480
Am I not doing this for you?

985
00:32:05,480 --> 00:32:06,000
Think about it!

986
00:32:06,000 --> 00:32:06,720
Didn't you get

987
00:32:06,720 --> 00:32:07,640
seriously injured because of him?

988
00:32:07,640 --> 00:32:08,240
Doesn't he have to take responsibility?

989
00:32:08,240 --> 00:32:10,200
You're right about everything, alright?

990
00:32:10,200 --> 00:32:12,240
If I'm right, why are you walking away?

991
00:32:12,240 --> 00:32:14,370
He has to take responsibility! You...

992
00:32:15,350 --> 00:32:16,680
You're so dense.

993
00:32:22,720 --> 00:32:23,750
I'm really sorry.

994
00:32:24,590 --> 00:32:26,750
I couldn't
stop my parents from doing that,

995
00:32:26,750 --> 00:32:28,510
and they've caused you a lot of trouble.

996
00:32:28,510 --> 00:32:29,110
It's okay.

997
00:32:29,700 --> 00:32:31,960
I know you didn't mean for this to happen.

998
00:32:35,070 --> 00:32:35,880
Cheng.

999
00:32:38,110 --> 00:32:39,970
I've liked you since we were kids.

1000
00:32:40,070 --> 00:32:42,330
I think you've known that for a long time.

1001
00:32:42,880 --> 00:32:43,880
I don't agree with

1002
00:32:44,070 --> 00:32:45,200
my parents pressuring you

1003
00:32:45,200 --> 00:32:45,830
this way.

1004
00:32:46,820 --> 00:32:47,750
But liking you

1005
00:32:48,720 --> 00:32:49,920
is my true intention.

1006
00:32:50,350 --> 00:32:51,070
Make way!

1007
00:32:52,440 --> 00:32:53,500
Make way! Make way!

1008
00:33:00,590 --> 00:33:01,110
What?

1009
00:33:01,790 --> 00:33:02,960
Getting a love confession from a beauty—

1010
00:33:02,960 --> 00:33:03,920
are you flustered?

1011
00:33:03,920 --> 00:33:04,680
Or touched?

1012
00:33:09,750 --> 00:33:10,830
Jiang Yan, actually...

1013
00:33:10,830 --> 00:33:11,440
Alright.

1014
00:33:12,310 --> 00:33:13,200
I'm not forcing you

1015
00:33:13,200 --> 00:33:14,060
to like me back.

1016
00:33:15,720 --> 00:33:17,250
That's not against the law,

1017
00:33:17,310 --> 00:33:19,440
and it doesn't affect our work, right?

1018
00:33:21,160 --> 00:33:21,690
Let's go.

1019
00:33:31,920 --> 00:33:32,380
Mr. Qiu,

1020
00:33:33,030 --> 00:33:34,750
the Du family's eldest son,

1021
00:33:34,750 --> 00:33:36,400
who had asked about the buyer of the vase

1022
00:33:36,400 --> 00:33:38,440
several times before, has come again.

1023
00:33:38,440 --> 00:33:39,900
He still wants to meet you.

1024
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:41,590
He said

1025
00:33:42,110 --> 00:33:44,240
you should take a look at this first...

1026
00:33:46,030 --> 00:33:47,830
then decide whether to meet him.

1027
00:33:55,750 --> 00:33:56,950
What was meant to come

1028
00:33:57,310 --> 00:33:58,350
has finally come.

1029
00:34:05,510 --> 00:34:07,270
He's just an antique dealer.

1030
00:34:07,550 --> 00:34:09,190
Why is he so hard to meet?

1031
00:34:13,510 --> 00:34:15,110
What did you send him just now?

1032
00:34:15,110 --> 00:34:16,239
Will he really come?

1033
00:34:17,219 --> 00:34:18,389
If it really is him,

1034
00:34:19,320 --> 00:34:20,630
he will definitely come.

1035
00:34:20,630 --> 00:34:21,510
Here I am.

1036
00:34:25,590 --> 00:34:26,920
Young Master Du, hello.

1037
00:34:28,320 --> 00:34:29,550
Ms. Xia, hello.

1038
00:34:31,480 --> 00:34:32,710
So you are Mr. Qiu?

1039
00:34:33,510 --> 00:34:35,840
Quite hard to get an appointment with you.

1040
00:34:36,060 --> 00:34:37,120
Mr. Qiu, seems like

1041
00:34:37,840 --> 00:34:39,770
you already knew who I was long ago.

1042
00:34:40,670 --> 00:34:43,270
Or perhaps I should call you
by another name...

1043
00:34:43,880 --> 00:34:44,590
Xu Zhongyi?

1044
00:34:53,000 --> 00:34:53,440
Yes.

1045
00:34:54,590 --> 00:34:56,190
Before you knew who I was,

1046
00:34:56,800 --> 00:34:57,860
I already knew you.

1047
00:34:58,590 --> 00:35:01,450
Thank you for taking care of
my mother all this time.

1048
00:35:04,920 --> 00:35:05,650
Please, sit.

1049
00:35:06,590 --> 00:35:07,120
Chai Hai,

1050
00:35:07,710 --> 00:35:08,510
serve the tea.

1051
00:35:08,590 --> 00:35:09,000
Okay.

1052
00:35:12,720 --> 00:35:13,770
Should I call you

1053
00:35:13,800 --> 00:35:14,880
Xu Zhongyi

1054
00:35:15,590 --> 00:35:17,030
or Mr. Qiu?

1055
00:35:19,280 --> 00:35:20,280
Poor Granny Yu.

1056
00:35:20,280 --> 00:35:22,120
She thought you were struggling
on the run all this time.

1057
00:35:22,120 --> 00:35:23,320
But it turns out you've become

1058
00:35:23,320 --> 00:35:25,030
quite a big shot now.

1059
00:35:25,800 --> 00:35:27,530
You're doing big business here

1060
00:35:27,960 --> 00:35:31,020
while letting your own mother
sweep streets back home.

1061
00:35:31,510 --> 00:35:32,150
A big shot?

1062
00:35:33,230 --> 00:35:34,150
Me—neither one thing

1063
00:35:34,150 --> 00:35:34,920
nor another—

1064
00:35:34,920 --> 00:35:35,840
a big shot?

1065
00:35:37,150 --> 00:35:38,710
Xu Zhongyi is dead.

1066
00:35:40,000 --> 00:35:41,130
The one who survived

1067
00:35:41,360 --> 00:35:42,440
is Mr. Qiu.

1068
00:35:44,440 --> 00:35:45,190
I went back secretly

1069
00:35:45,190 --> 00:35:46,850
and checked on her a few times.

1070
00:35:47,230 --> 00:35:49,050
But I was too ashamed to reunite with her,

1071
00:35:49,050 --> 00:35:50,210
and I didn't dare.

1072
00:35:51,110 --> 00:35:51,570
Because

1073
00:35:52,400 --> 00:35:54,530
until I kill my enemy with my own hands,

1074
00:35:54,960 --> 00:35:56,130
I have no right

1075
00:35:56,510 --> 00:35:58,240
to reclaim the name Xu Zhongyi.

1076
00:35:59,110 --> 00:36:00,370
What exactly happened

1077
00:36:01,030 --> 00:36:02,030
over 20 years ago?

1078
00:36:03,970 --> 00:36:07,810
[1967]

1079
00:36:20,320 --> 00:36:21,250
Don't be afraid.

1080
00:36:21,280 --> 00:36:22,440
Once they get us a boat,

1081
00:36:22,440 --> 00:36:24,440
we'll be fine when we reach Nanyang.

1082
00:36:39,050 --> 00:36:40,190
Zhongyi, it's me.

1083
00:36:41,090 --> 00:36:42,090
The boat is ready.

1084
00:36:42,400 --> 00:36:43,530
You can leave today.

1085
00:36:50,230 --> 00:36:51,480
It's raining so heavily.

1086
00:36:51,480 --> 00:36:52,410
Is the boat safe?

1087
00:36:56,480 --> 00:36:57,080
It's safe.

1088
00:38:21,760 --> 00:38:23,320
Finding the valuables is the priority.

1089
00:38:23,320 --> 00:38:24,720
He's not going to make it.

1090
00:39:11,760 --> 00:39:12,560
That bastard—

1091
00:39:12,840 --> 00:39:15,040
he lied about helping me
find a boat to Nanyang.

1092
00:39:15,040 --> 00:39:17,250
In reality, he was after my antiques.

1093
00:39:18,070 --> 00:39:18,870
Fortunately,

1094
00:39:19,280 --> 00:39:20,280
I hadn't brought all of them

1095
00:39:20,280 --> 00:39:21,110
with me.

1096
00:39:21,630 --> 00:39:23,230
I'd buried some beforehand.

1097
00:39:24,280 --> 00:39:24,800
Later,

1098
00:39:25,070 --> 00:39:26,920
it was those remaining few pieces

1099
00:39:26,920 --> 00:39:28,650
that kept me going until today.

1100
00:39:30,000 --> 00:39:31,200
I didn't dare go home,

1101
00:39:31,550 --> 00:39:33,280
afraid of bringing harm to my family,

1102
00:39:33,280 --> 00:39:33,840
so

1103
00:39:34,280 --> 00:39:35,440
I changed my identity

1104
00:39:35,440 --> 00:39:36,840
and lived under a false name.

1105
00:39:36,840 --> 00:39:37,320
Later,

1106
00:39:37,670 --> 00:39:39,800
I finally built something for myself.

1107
00:39:40,070 --> 00:39:40,870
I stayed here,

1108
00:39:41,230 --> 00:39:43,360
just waiting for the day of my revenge.

1109
00:39:44,480 --> 00:39:45,880
The bastard he mentioned

1110
00:39:46,070 --> 00:39:47,800
is even more ruthless than I am.

1111
00:39:51,540 --> 00:39:53,340
You may have been afraid before,

1112
00:39:53,670 --> 00:39:55,530
but now it's just pure arrogance.

1113
00:39:56,360 --> 00:39:57,190
Since you've already established yourself

1114
00:39:57,190 --> 00:39:58,070
as Mr. Qiu

1115
00:39:58,760 --> 00:40:00,480
and can live well in Gangdao,

1116
00:40:01,070 --> 00:40:02,280
why not go back?

1117
00:40:04,190 --> 00:40:05,510
I haven't taken my revenge yet.

1118
00:40:05,510 --> 00:40:07,030
I haven't killed my enemy
with my own hands,

1119
00:40:07,030 --> 00:40:08,830
so I have no face to see my family.

1120
00:40:12,150 --> 00:40:13,230
You have a hundred ways

1121
00:40:13,230 --> 00:40:14,800
to seek justice,

1122
00:40:15,280 --> 00:40:16,320
yet you chose

1123
00:40:16,320 --> 00:40:18,320
the most stubborn and outdated one.

1124
00:40:18,480 --> 00:40:19,440
Just look at

1125
00:40:19,760 --> 00:40:21,760
what era we're living in—it's the 90s now.

1126
00:40:21,760 --> 00:40:23,190
Yet you're still here talking about

1127
00:40:23,190 --> 00:40:24,710
killing your enemy with your own hands.

1128
00:40:24,710 --> 00:40:25,360
Have you ever thought about

1129
00:40:25,360 --> 00:40:26,620
what Granny Yu thinks?

1130
00:40:27,360 --> 00:40:28,670
If she knew about this,

1131
00:40:29,280 --> 00:40:30,880
what would she want you to do?

1132
00:40:35,550 --> 00:40:36,150
I'm sorry.

1133
00:40:36,800 --> 00:40:38,000
I can't truly

1134
00:40:38,000 --> 00:40:39,400
put myself in your shoes,

1135
00:40:39,480 --> 00:40:40,320
but at the same time,

1136
00:40:40,320 --> 00:40:43,120
you've never really considered
Granny Yu either.

1137
00:40:43,400 --> 00:40:45,630
I still have a conference
to attend in Jiangcheng,

1138
00:40:45,630 --> 00:40:46,760
so I can stay here

1139
00:40:46,760 --> 00:40:48,710
until tomorrow afternoon at the latest.

1140
00:40:48,710 --> 00:40:49,360
Whether you want

1141
00:40:49,360 --> 00:40:51,160
to go back with me to see Granny Yu

1142
00:40:51,400 --> 00:40:52,510
is up to you.

1143
00:40:57,150 --> 00:40:58,210
Mr. Qiu, I heard you

1144
00:40:58,400 --> 00:41:00,060
hold an antique auction here.

1145
00:41:00,400 --> 00:41:02,000
I'd love to see it for myself.

1146
00:41:02,190 --> 00:41:04,000
I need to pick out a gift

1147
00:41:04,000 --> 00:41:05,280
for my project's property consultant.

1148
00:41:05,280 --> 00:41:07,280
Mr. Qiu, why don't you take me there?

1149
00:41:07,400 --> 00:41:07,800
Okay.

1150
00:41:08,960 --> 00:41:09,890
It's just ahead.

1151
00:41:10,630 --> 00:41:11,190
Let's go.

1152
00:41:13,670 --> 00:41:14,200
Let's go.

1153
00:41:15,400 --> 00:41:16,030
Bidder 11

1154
00:41:16,150 --> 00:41:18,230
bids $1.1 million. Going twice!

1155
00:41:18,710 --> 00:41:19,360
Bidder 11

1156
00:41:19,400 --> 00:41:21,630
bids $1.1 million. Going three times!

1157
00:41:22,030 --> 00:41:23,110
Sold!

1158
00:41:23,550 --> 00:41:24,480
Congratulations

1159
00:41:24,480 --> 00:41:25,710
on winning this

1160
00:41:25,760 --> 00:41:27,550
rare and precious

1161
00:41:27,800 --> 00:41:29,710
Yuan Dynasty octagonal "Yuhuchun" vase

1162
00:41:29,710 --> 00:41:31,570
with an underglaze-red dragon motif.

1163
00:41:31,570 --> 00:41:32,770
The one on the far side

1164
00:41:32,800 --> 00:41:34,400
is that loser, Du Zhaoji.

1165
00:41:34,480 --> 00:41:35,880
Please have the item

1166
00:41:36,070 --> 00:41:37,150
packaged and delivered

1167
00:41:37,150 --> 00:41:38,920
to VIP No. 11's storage.

1168
00:41:39,400 --> 00:41:40,150
Thank you.

1169
00:41:41,080 --> 00:41:42,120
So next,

1170
00:41:42,150 --> 00:41:43,280
let's move on

1171
00:41:43,320 --> 00:41:44,670
to our second piece.

1172
00:41:45,030 --> 00:41:46,030
Someone you know?

1173
00:41:46,040 --> 00:41:47,810
A very rare and precious piece.

1174
00:41:47,840 --> 00:41:48,320
No.

1175
00:41:48,550 --> 00:41:50,710
It's also from the Yuan Dynasty.

1176
00:41:51,070 --> 00:41:52,270
Please, bring it out.

1177
00:41:58,360 --> 00:41:59,480
The second lot

1178
00:41:59,510 --> 00:42:02,840
is a Yuan Dynasty hand-painted
Persian blue-rimmed basin.

1179
00:42:03,110 --> 00:42:05,510
The starting bid is $500,000.

1180
00:42:10,230 --> 00:42:13,400
Bidder 3, $550,000, first call.

1181
00:42:13,630 --> 00:42:14,650
Any other bids?

1182
00:42:14,800 --> 00:42:15,630
Here, Bidder 7.

1183
00:42:15,630 --> 00:42:16,090
Mr. Qiu,

1184
00:42:16,440 --> 00:42:17,590
how did Ms. Xia manage to

1185
00:42:17,590 --> 00:42:19,050
find you here so suddenly?

1186
00:42:19,480 --> 00:42:21,140
Naturally, someone told her.

1187
00:42:21,880 --> 00:42:22,680
It's a warning

1188
00:42:23,320 --> 00:42:25,760
that he already knows my weakness.

1189
00:42:27,110 --> 00:42:28,170
It doesn't matter.

1190
00:42:28,360 --> 00:42:29,880
Isn't the basis of mutual exploitation

1191
00:42:29,880 --> 00:42:31,010
that each side holds

1192
00:42:31,150 --> 00:42:32,610
something over the other?

1193
00:42:33,760 --> 00:42:34,490
Fair enough.

1194
00:42:37,030 --> 00:42:39,230
Bidder 3, $750,000, second call!

1195
00:42:42,920 --> 00:42:43,650
Comrade Xia,

1196
00:42:44,240 --> 00:42:45,190
I finally found you.

1197
00:42:45,190 --> 00:42:46,230
I'm so happy.

1198
00:42:47,440 --> 00:42:48,280
Ye Xiaoqiong?

1199
00:42:49,190 --> 00:42:49,840
I never expected

1200
00:42:49,840 --> 00:42:51,110
to see you in Gangdao.

1201
00:42:51,630 --> 00:42:53,280
Looks like you're doing well.

1202
00:42:53,280 --> 00:42:54,630
Didn't you say you were going to Hushi

1203
00:42:54,630 --> 00:42:55,960
to look for your family?

1204
00:42:56,190 --> 00:42:57,710
There was no family to find.

1205
00:42:57,710 --> 00:42:58,480
After staying in Hushi

1206
00:42:58,480 --> 00:42:59,710
for a while,

1207
00:42:59,760 --> 00:43:01,760
I eventually made my way to Gangdao.

1208
00:43:01,880 --> 00:43:02,480
I got lucky

1209
00:43:02,760 --> 00:43:05,090
and landed a job
as a clerk in a big company.

1210
00:43:09,800 --> 00:43:10,700
If back then

1211
00:43:10,760 --> 00:43:11,760
you hadn't rescued me

1212
00:43:11,760 --> 00:43:12,960
from those traffickers

1213
00:43:12,960 --> 00:43:13,620
on the train

1214
00:43:14,190 --> 00:43:15,190
and lent me money,

1215
00:43:15,670 --> 00:43:17,070
I probably would've lost

1216
00:43:17,230 --> 00:43:18,360
all hope in life.

1217
00:43:19,030 --> 00:43:20,280
So, your kindness

1218
00:43:20,480 --> 00:43:21,280
can never be repaid

1219
00:43:21,280 --> 00:43:22,320
with money.

1220
00:43:23,280 --> 00:43:24,150
I originally thought about

1221
00:43:24,150 --> 00:43:25,480
wiring the money to you,

1222
00:43:25,760 --> 00:43:26,830
but I felt

1223
00:43:26,960 --> 00:43:28,190
I had to thank you

1224
00:43:28,510 --> 00:43:29,630
in person.

1225
00:43:30,190 --> 00:43:31,120
So, Comrade Xia,

1226
00:43:31,280 --> 00:43:32,410
please accept this.

1227
00:43:36,630 --> 00:43:37,110
No need.

1228
00:43:38,190 --> 00:43:39,850
Just repay what you borrowed.

1229
00:43:39,920 --> 00:43:41,000
I only lent you

1230
00:43:41,000 --> 00:43:41,960
100 yuan back then.

1231
00:43:41,960 --> 00:43:43,440
It was barely enough for travel expenses.

1232
00:43:43,440 --> 00:43:44,670
It was your own hard work

1233
00:43:44,670 --> 00:43:45,320
that got you

1234
00:43:45,320 --> 00:43:46,580
this decent job today.

1235
00:43:48,030 --> 00:43:48,960
Actually,

1236
00:43:49,800 --> 00:43:51,030
I didn't come to you today

1237
00:43:51,030 --> 00:43:52,230
just to catch up.

1238
00:43:53,590 --> 00:43:54,670
Do you have time

1239
00:43:54,670 --> 00:43:55,400
to talk?
